        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 2:32AM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 232 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Ball to 6 miles east of Merryville.
Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cheneyville, Mansura, Turkey Creek, Bayou Chicot, Bunkie, Esler
Regional Airport, Calcasieu, Oakdale, Lake Ophelia National Wildlife
Refuge, Elmer, Kingsville, Glenmora, Allen Parish Airport, Forest
Hill, Sugartown, Poland, Hessmer, Kolin, Beaver, and Alexandria.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 48 and 87.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
